t.com/images/2026/06/07/magazine/07mag-ididit-sleep/07mag-ididit-sleep-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Photo illustration by Hannah Whitaker</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Tesla Driver Using Autopilot Crashes Into Home in Texas and Kills a Woman, Officials Say</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/21/us/tesla-autopilot-crash-texas.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The driver told investigators he was using the vehicle’s automated-driver system when the vehicle left the roadway and crashed into a house in Harris County, Texas.</description><dc:creator>Johnny Diaz</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:49:15 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Driverless Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Self-Driving Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fatalities</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">casualties</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Crash</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Harris County</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Katy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/21/multimedia/21xp-tesla-vtmq/21xp-tesla-vtmq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mike Blake/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>The dashboard of a Tesla model using a driver-assistance system in California.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>New Super PAC, the Guardrails Alliance, Aims to Rally Tech Workers to Help Limit A.I.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-super-pac-guardrails-alliance.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-super-pac-guardrails-alliance.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-super-pac-guardrails-alliance.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The Guardrails Alliance, which has raised $5 million, is positioning itself as a populist effort that will take on the pro-A.I. interests trying to influence this year’s elections.</description><dc:creator>Mike Isaac and Theodore Schleifer</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 09:02:32 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">PACs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Guardrails Alliance</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">2026 Midterm Elections</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Greg Brockman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Leading the Future</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Populism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Leah Hunt-Hendrix</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Shaunna Thomas</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Alex Bores</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">House races</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Congressional elections</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/18/multimedia/18biz-ai-superpac-Shaunna-qjlk/18biz-ai-superpac-Shaunna-qjlk-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Tierney L. Cross for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Shaunna Thomas is a founder of the Guardrails Alliance, a new super PAC trying to take on moneyed entities that oppose reining in artificial intelligence.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Tech Workers Maxed Out Their A.I. Use. Now They’re Trying to Minimize It.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-token-minimizing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-token-minimizing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/18/technology/ai-token-minimizing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Artificial intelligence is expensive to use, many companies discovered. That has led to a new era of saving costs.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 14:17:26 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jobs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des"